    "Toral (2019) reached similar conclusions focusing on automatic post-editing, demonstrating its simpler and more normalized nature compared to human post-edited or translated texts.",
    "Both these observations can, in turn, be linked directly to gender bias in translations.",
    "Looking back at Figure 1, it is likely that some of the potential translations are way more common in the data than others.",
    "The model would strengthen the more frequently occurring connections and weaken those that are more rarely observed in the data.",
    "In a follow-up paper, Vanmassenhove et al. (2021) conducted experiments where they train a model with which they then translate the original training data."
